    "title": "Constant-time operations on x86 and ARM",
    "body": "\"Intel and ARM recently published documentation that says that no instructions\r\nare guaranteed to be constant-time with respect to their data operands, unless a\r\n\"data independent timing\" flag in the IA32_UARCH_MISC_CTL register (Intel) or\r\nDIT register (arm64) is set.\r\n\r\n(quote from https://lkml.org/lkml/2022/8/25/1372)\r\n\r\nI haven't had a deep look so far. We probably report this also to Core. ",
